			<p class="padding-top">It should be noted that while in modern English ‘the’ is considered an <abbr
					title="Articles are words that define a noun as specific or unspecific">article</abbr>, in Old
				English ‘the’ is considered to be a demonstrative pronoun because it can be used on its own. For
				example, examine the sentence below and you will see that the same demonstrative pronouns
				we have been using for 'the' can be used in much the same was as <strong>that</strong>,
				<strong>he</strong>, <strong>she</strong>, <strong>it</strong>.
				For example, the first sentence could be translated as 'That one was a mournful woman' and the
				second
				sentence could be translated as 'She is my daughter' or 'That is my daughter'.
			</p>
