			<p class="padding-top">Demonstratives can also be used to add more specificity. In modern English, the
				demonstrative pronouns would be <strong>this</strong>, <strong>that</strong>, <strong>these</strong>,
				<strong>those</strong>. They are sometimes known as ‘pointing
				pronouns’ as they are often used when referencing specific objects or providing location.
				For example, examine the sentence: The King gave this ring to his wife and that ring to his daughter.
			</p>
